80#define is_eol_tok(tok) ((tok) == '\n' || (tok) == ';' || (tok) == 0)
81#define is_eol() is_eol_tok(curtok)
82
83#define get_next_token() (curtok = gas_parser_lex(&curval, parser_gas))
84
85static void
86get_peek_token(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
87{
88 char savech = parser_gas->tokch;
89 if (parser_gas->peek_token != NONE)
90 yasm_internal_error(N_("can only have one token of lookahead"));
91 parser_gas->peek_token =
92 gas_parser_lex(&parser_gas->peek_tokval, parser_gas);
93 parser_gas->peek_tokch = parser_gas->tokch;
94 parser_gas->tokch = savech;
95}

97static void
98destroy_curtok_(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
99{
100 if (curtok < 256)
101 ;
102 else switch ((enum tokentype)curtok) {
103 case INTNUM:
104 yasm_intnum_destroy(curval.intn);
105 break;
106 case FLTNUM:
107 yasm_floatnum_destroy(curval.flt);
108 break;
109 case ID:
110 case LABEL:
111 case STRING:
112 yasm_xfree(curval.str.contents);
113 break;
114 default:
115 break;
116 }
117 curtok = NONE; /* sanity */
118}
119#define destroy_curtok() destroy_curtok_(parser_gas)
120
121/* Eat all remaining tokens to EOL, discarding all of them. If there's any
122 * intervening tokens, generates an error (junk at end of line).
123 */
124static void
125demand_eol_(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
126{
127 if (is_eol())
128 return;
129
130 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
131 N_("junk at end of line, first unrecognized character is `%c'"),
132 parser_gas->tokch);
133
134 do {
135 destroy_curtok();
136 get_next_token();
137 } while (!is_eol());
138}
139#define demand_eol() demand_eol_(parser_gas)
140
141static int
142expect_(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, int token)
143{
144 static char strch[] = "` '";
145 const char *str;
146
147 if (curtok == token)
148 return 1;
149
150 switch (token) {
151 case INTNUM: str = "integer"; break;
152 case FLTNUM: str = "floating point value"; break;
153 case STRING: str = "string"; break;
154 case REG: str = "register"; break;
155 case REGGROUP: str = "register group"; break;
156 case SEGREG: str = "segment register"; break;
157 case TARGETMOD: str = "target modifier"; break;
158 case LEFT_OP: str = "<<"; break;
159 case RIGHT_OP: str = ">>"; break;
160 case ID: str = "identifier"; break;
161 case LABEL: str = "label"; break;
162 default:
163 strch[1] = token;
164 str = strch;
165 break;
166 }
167 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_PARSE, "expected %s", str);
168 destroy_curtok();
169 return 0;
170}
171#define expect(token) expect_(parser_gas, token)

173static yasm_bytecode *
174parse_line(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
175{
176 yasm_bytecode *bc;
177 yasm_expr *e;
178 yasm_valparamhead vps;
179 char *id;
180 const dir_lookup *dir;
181
182 if (is_eol())
183 return NULL;
184
185 bc = parse_instr(parser_gas);
186 if (bc)
187 return bc;
188
189 switch (curtok) {
190 case ID:
191 id = ID_val;
192
193 /* See if it's a gas-specific directive */
194 dir = (const dir_lookup *)HAMT_search(parser_gas->dirs, id);
195 if (dir) {
196 parser_gas->state = dir->newstate;
197 get_next_token(); /* ID */
198 return dir->handler(parser_gas, dir->param);
199 }
200
201 get_next_token(); /* ID */
202 if (curtok == ':') {
203 /* Label */
204 parser_gas->state = INITIAL;
205 get_next_token(); /* : */
206 define_label(parser_gas, id, 0);
207 return parse_line(parser_gas);
208 } else if (curtok == '=') {
209 /* EQU */
210 /* TODO: allow redefinition, assigning to . (same as .org) */
211 parser_gas->state = INITIAL;
212 get_next_token(); /* = */
213 e = parse_expr(parser_gas);
214 if (e)
215 yasm_symtab_define_equ(p_symtab, id, e, cur_line);
216 else
217 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
218 N_("expression expected after `%s'"), "=");
219 yasm_xfree(id);
220 return NULL;
221 }
222
223 /* possibly a directive; try to parse it */
224 parse_dirvals(parser_gas, &vps);
225 if (!yasm_object_directive(p_object, id, "gas", &vps, NULL,
226 cur_line)) {
227 yasm_vps_delete(&vps);
228 yasm_xfree(id);
229 return NULL;
230 }
231 yasm_vps_delete(&vps);
232 if (id[0] == '.')
233 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
234 N_("directive `%s' not recognized"), id);
235 else
236 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
237 N_("instruction not recognized: `%s'"), id);
238 yasm_xfree(id);
239 return NULL;
240 case LABEL:
241 define_label(parser_gas, LABEL_val, 0);
242 get_next_token(); /* LABEL */
243 return parse_line(parser_gas);
244 case CPP_LINE_MARKER:
245 get_next_token();
246 cpp_line_marker(parser_gas);
247 return NULL;
248 case NASM_LINE_MARKER:
249 get_next_token();
250 nasm_line_marker(parser_gas);
251 return NULL;
252 default:
253 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
254 N_("label or instruction expected at start of line"));
255 return NULL;
256 }
257}

259/*
260 Handle line markers generated by cpp.
261
262 We expect a positive integer (line) followed by a string (filename). If we
263 fail to find either of these, we treat the line as a comment. There is a
264 possibility of false positives (mistaking a comment for a line marker, when
265 the comment is not intended as a line marker) but this cannot be avoided
266 without adding a filter to the input before passing it to cpp.
267
268 This function is only called if the preprocessor was 'cpp', since the
269 CPP_LINE_MARKER token isn't generated for any other preprocessor. With any
270 other preprocessor, anything after a '#' is always treated as a comment.
271*/
272static void
273cpp_line_marker(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
274{
275 yasm_valparamhead vps;
276 yasm_valparam *vp;
277 unsigned long line;
278 char *filename;
279
280 /* Line number. */
281 if (curtok != INTNUM) {
282 /* Skip over a comment. */
283 while (curtok != '\n')
284 get_next_token();
285
286 return;
287 }
288
289 if (yasm_intnum_sign(INTNUM_val) < 0) {
290 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
291 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
292 N_("line number is negative"));
293 return;
294 }
295
296 line = yasm_intnum_get_uint(INTNUM_val);
297
298 /*
299 Set to (line - 1) since the directive indicates that the *next* line
300 will have the number given.
301
302 cpp should never produce line=0, but the if keeps us safe just incase.
303 */
304 if (line != 0)
305 line--;
306
307 yasm_intnum_destroy(INTNUM_val);
308 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
309
310 /* File name, in quotes. */
311 if (curtok != STRING) {
312 /* Skip over a comment. */
313 while (curtok != '\n')
314 get_next_token();
315
316 return;
317 }
318
319 filename = STRING_val.contents;
320 get_next_token();
321
322 /* Set linemap. */
323 yasm_linemap_set(parser_gas->linemap, filename, 0, line, 1);
324
325 /*
326 The first line marker in the file (which should be on the first line
327 of the file) will give us the name of the source file. This information
328 needs to be passed on to the debug format module.
329 */
330 if (parser_gas->seen_line_marker == 0) {
331 parser_gas->seen_line_marker = 1;
332
333 yasm_vps_initialize(&vps);
334 vp = yasm_vp_create_string(NULL, filename);
335 yasm_vps_append(&vps, vp);
336
337 yasm_object_directive(p_object, ".file", "gas", &vps, NULL, cur_line);
338
339 yasm_vps_delete(&vps);
340 } else
341 yasm_xfree(filename);
342
343 /* Skip flags. */
344 while (1) {
345 switch (curtok) {
346 case INTNUM:
347 break;
348
349 case '\n':
350 return;
351
352 default:
353 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
354 N_("junk at end of cpp line marker"));
355 return;
356 }
357 get_next_token();
358 }
359}

361/*
362 Handle line markers generated by the nasm preproc.
363
364 We expect a positive integer (line) followed by a plus sign, followed by
365 another positive integer, followed by a string (filename).
366
367 This function is only called if the preprocessor was 'nasm', since the
368 NASM_LINE_MARKER token isn't generated for any other preprocessor.
369*/
370static void
371nasm_line_marker(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
372{
373 yasm_valparamhead vps;
374 yasm_valparam *vp;
375 unsigned long line, incr;
376 char *filename;
377
378 /* Line number. */
379 if (!expect(INTNUM)) return;
380
381 if (yasm_intnum_sign(INTNUM_val) < 0) {
382 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
383 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
384 N_("line number is negative"));
385 return;
386 }
387
388 line = yasm_intnum_get_uint(INTNUM_val);
389
390 /*
391 Set to (line - 1) since the directive indicates that the *next* line
392 will have the number given.
393
394 cpp should never produce line=0, but the if keeps us safe just incase.
395 */
396 if (line != 0)
397 line--;
398
399 yasm_intnum_destroy(INTNUM_val);
400 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
401
402 if (!expect('+')) return;
403 get_next_token(); /* + */
404
405 /* Line number increment. */
406 if (!expect(INTNUM)) return;
407
408 if (yasm_intnum_sign(INTNUM_val) < 0) {
409 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
410 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
411 N_("line increment is negative"));
412 return;
413 }
414
415 incr = yasm_intnum_get_uint(INTNUM_val);
416 yasm_intnum_destroy(INTNUM_val);
417
418 /* File name is not in quotes, so need to switch to a different tokenizer
419 * state.
420 */
421 parser_gas->state = NASM_FILENAME;
422 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
423 if (!expect(STRING)) {
424 parser_gas->state = INITIAL;
425 return;
426 }
427
428 filename = STRING_val.contents;
429
430 /* Set linemap. */
431 yasm_linemap_set(parser_gas->linemap, filename, 0, line, incr);
432
433 /*
434 The first line marker in the file (which should be on the first line
435 of the file) will give us the name of the source file. This information
436 needs to be passed on to the debug format module.
437 */
438 if (parser_gas->seen_line_marker == 0) {
439 parser_gas->seen_line_marker = 1;
440
441 yasm_vps_initialize(&vps);
442 vp = yasm_vp_create_string(NULL, filename);
443 yasm_vps_append(&vps, vp);
444
445 yasm_object_directive(p_object, ".file", "gas", &vps, NULL, cur_line);
446
447 yasm_vps_delete(&vps);
448 } else
449 yasm_xfree(filename);
450
451 /* We need to poke back on the \n that was consumed by the tokenizer */
452 parser_gas->peek_token = '\n';
453 get_next_token();
454}

456/* Line directive */
457static yasm_bytecode *
458dir_line(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, unsigned int param)
459{
460 if (!expect(INTNUM)) return NULL;
461 if (yasm_intnum_sign(INTNUM_val) < 0) {
462 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
463 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
464 N_("line number is negative"));
465 return NULL;
466 }
467
468 parser_gas->dir_line = yasm_intnum_get_uint(INTNUM_val);
469 yasm_intnum_destroy(INTNUM_val);
470 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
471
472 if (parser_gas->dir_fileline == 3) {
473 /* Have both file and line */
474 yasm_linemap_set(parser_gas->linemap, NULL, 0,
475 parser_gas->dir_line, 1);
476 } else if (parser_gas->dir_fileline == 1) {
477 /* Had previous file directive only */
478 parser_gas->dir_fileline = 3;
479 yasm_linemap_set(parser_gas->linemap, parser_gas->dir_file, 0,
480 parser_gas->dir_line, 1);
481 } else {
482 /* Didn't see file yet */
483 parser_gas->dir_fileline = 2;
484 }
485 return NULL;
486}

488/* Alignment directives */
489
490static yasm_bytecode *
491dir_align(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, unsigned int param)
492{
493 yasm_expr *bound, *fill=NULL, *maxskip=NULL;
494
495 bound = parse_expr(parser_gas);
496 if (!bound) {
497 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
498 N_(".align directive must specify alignment"));
499 return NULL;
500 }
501
502 if (curtok == ',') {
503 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
504 fill = parse_expr(parser_gas);
505 if (curtok == ',') {
506 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
507 maxskip = parse_expr(parser_gas);
508 }
509 }
510
511 return gas_parser_align(parser_gas, cursect, bound, fill, maxskip,
512 (int)param);
513}

515static yasm_bytecode *
516dir_org(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, unsigned int param)
517{
518 yasm_intnum *start, *value=NULL;
519 yasm_bytecode *bc;
520
521 /* TODO: support expr instead of intnum */
522 if (!expect(INTNUM)) return NULL;
523 start = INTNUM_val;
524 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
525
526 if (curtok == ',') {
527 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
528 /* TODO: support expr instead of intnum */
529 if (!expect(INTNUM)) return NULL;
530 value = INTNUM_val;
531 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
532 }
533 if (value) {
534 bc = yasm_bc_create_org(yasm_intnum_get_uint(start),
535 yasm_intnum_get_uint(value), cur_line);
536 yasm_intnum_destroy(value);
537 } else
538 bc = yasm_bc_create_org(yasm_intnum_get_uint(start), 0,
539 cur_line);
540 yasm_intnum_destroy(start);
541 return bc;
542}

556static yasm_bytecode *
557dir_comm(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, unsigned int is_lcomm)
558{
559 yasm_expr *align = NULL;
560 /*@null@*/ /*@dependent@*/ yasm_symrec *sym;
561 char *id;
562 yasm_expr *e;
563
564 if (!expect(ID)) return NULL;
565 id = ID_val;
566 get_next_token(); /* ID */
567 if (!expect(',')) {
568 yasm_xfree(id);
569 return NULL;
570 }
571 get_next_token(); /* , */
572 e = parse_expr(parser_gas);
573 if (!e) {
574 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("size expected for `%s'"),
575 ".COMM");
576 return NULL;
577 }
578 if (curtok == ',') {
579 /* Optional alignment expression */
580 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
581 align = parse_expr(parser_gas);
582 }
583 /* If already explicitly declared local, treat like LCOMM */
584 if (is_lcomm
585 || ((sym = yasm_symtab_get(p_symtab, id))
586 && yasm_symrec_get_visibility(sym) == YASM_SYM_DLOCAL)) {
587 define_lcomm(parser_gas, id, e, align);
588 } else if (align) {
589 /* Give third parameter as objext valparam */
590 yasm_valparamhead *extvps = yasm_vps_create();
591 yasm_valparam *vp = yasm_vp_create_expr(NULL, align);
592 yasm_vps_append(extvps, vp);
593
594 sym = yasm_symtab_declare(p_symtab, id, YASM_SYM_COMMON,
595 cur_line);
596 yasm_symrec_set_common_size(sym, e);
597 yasm_symrec_set_objext_valparams(sym, extvps);
598
599 yasm_xfree(id);
600 } else {
601 sym = yasm_symtab_declare(p_symtab, id, YASM_SYM_COMMON,
602 cur_line);
603 yasm_symrec_set_common_size(sym, e);
604 yasm_xfree(id);
605 }
606 return NULL;
607}

639/* Empty space / fill data definition directives */
640
641static yasm_bytecode *
642dir_zero(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, unsigned int param)
643{
644 yasm_bytecode *bc;
645 yasm_datavalhead dvs;
646 yasm_expr *e = parse_expr(parser_gas);
647 if (!e) {
648 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
649 N_("expression expected after `%s'"), ".ZERO");
650 return NULL;
651 }
652
653 yasm_dvs_initialize(&dvs);
654 yasm_dvs_append(&dvs, yasm_dv_create_expr(
655 p_expr_new_ident(yasm_expr_int(yasm_intnum_create_uint(0)))));
656 bc = yasm_bc_create_data(&dvs, 1, 0, p_object->arch, cur_line);
657 yasm_bc_set_multiple(bc, e);
658 return bc;
659}
660
661static yasm_bytecode *
662dir_skip(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, unsigned int param)
663{
664 yasm_expr *e, *e_val;
665 yasm_bytecode *bc;
666 yasm_datavalhead dvs;
667
668 e = parse_expr(parser_gas);
669 if (!e) {
670 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
671 N_("expression expected after `%s'"), ".SKIP");
672 return NULL;
673 }
674 if (curtok != ',')
675 return yasm_bc_create_reserve(e, 1, cur_line);
676 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
677 e_val = parse_expr(parser_gas);
678 yasm_dvs_initialize(&dvs);
679 yasm_dvs_append(&dvs, yasm_dv_create_expr(e_val));
680 bc = yasm_bc_create_data(&dvs, 1, 0, p_object->arch, cur_line);
681
682 yasm_bc_set_multiple(bc, e);
683 return bc;
684}

686/* fill data definition directive */
687static yasm_bytecode *
688dir_fill(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, unsigned int param)
689{
690 yasm_expr *sz=NULL, *val=NULL;
691 yasm_expr *e = parse_expr(parser_gas);
692 if (!e) {
693 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
694 N_("expression expected after `%s'"), ".FILL");
695 return NULL;
696 }
697 if (curtok == ',') {
698 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
699 sz = parse_expr(parser_gas);
700 if (curtok == ',') {
701 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
702 val = parse_expr(parser_gas);
703 }
704 }
705 return gas_parser_dir_fill(parser_gas, e, sz, val);
706}

731static yasm_bytecode *
732dir_section(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, unsigned int param)
733{
734 /* DIR_SECTION ID ',' STRING ',' '@' ID ',' dirvals */
735 char *sectname, *flags = NULL, *type = NULL;
736 yasm_valparamhead vps;
737 int have_vps = 0;
738
739 if (!expect(ID)) return NULL;
740 sectname = ID_val;
741 get_next_token(); /* ID */
742
743 if (curtok == ',') {
744 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
745 if (!expect(STRING)) {
746 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
747 N_("flag string expected"));
748 yasm_xfree(sectname);
749 return NULL;
750 }
751 flags = STRING_val.contents;
752 get_next_token(); /* STRING */
753 }
754
755 if (curtok == ',') {
756 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
757 if (!expect('@')) {
758 yasm_xfree(sectname);
759 yasm_xfree(flags);
760 return NULL;
761 }
762 get_next_token(); /* '@' */
763 if (!expect(ID)) {
764 yasm_xfree(sectname);
765 yasm_xfree(flags);
766 return NULL;
767 }
768 type = ID_val;
769 get_next_token(); /* ID */
770 }
771
772 if (curtok == ',') {
773 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
774 if (parse_dirvals(parser_gas, &vps))
775 have_vps = 1;
776 }
777
778 gas_switch_section(parser_gas, sectname, flags, type,
779 have_vps ? &vps : NULL, 0);
780 yasm_xfree(sectname);
781 yasm_xfree(flags);
782 return NULL;
783}

812static yasm_bytecode *
813dir_file(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, unsigned int param)
814{
815 yasm_valparamhead vps;
816 yasm_valparam *vp;
817
818 if (curtok == STRING) {
819 /* No file number; this form also sets the assembler's
820 * internal line number.
821 */
822 char *filename = STRING_val.contents;
823
824 get_next_token(); /* STRING */
825 if (parser_gas->dir_fileline == 3) {
826 /* Have both file and line */
827 const char *old_fn;
828 unsigned long old_line;
829
830 yasm_linemap_lookup(parser_gas->linemap, cur_line, &old_fn,
831 &old_line);
832 yasm_linemap_set(parser_gas->linemap, filename, 0, old_line,
833 1);
834 } else if (parser_gas->dir_fileline == 2) {
835 /* Had previous line directive only */
836 parser_gas->dir_fileline = 3;
837 yasm_linemap_set(parser_gas->linemap, filename, 0,
838 parser_gas->dir_line, 1);
839 } else {
840 /* Didn't see line yet, save file */
841 parser_gas->dir_fileline = 1;
842 if (parser_gas->dir_file)
843 yasm_xfree(parser_gas->dir_file);
844 parser_gas->dir_file = yasm__xstrdup(filename);
845 }
846
847 /* Pass change along to debug format */
848 yasm_vps_initialize(&vps);
849 vp = yasm_vp_create_string(NULL, filename);
850 yasm_vps_append(&vps, vp);
851
852 yasm_object_directive(p_object, ".file", "gas", &vps, NULL,
853 cur_line);
854
855 yasm_vps_delete(&vps);
856 return NULL;
857 }
858
859 /* fileno filename form */
860 yasm_vps_initialize(&vps);
861
862 if (!expect(INTNUM)) return NULL;
863 vp = yasm_vp_create_expr(NULL,
864 p_expr_new_ident(yasm_expr_int(INTNUM_val)));
865 yasm_vps_append(&vps, vp);
866 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
867
868 if (!expect(STRING)) {
869 yasm_vps_delete(&vps);
870 return NULL;
871 }
872 vp = yasm_vp_create_string(NULL, STRING_val.contents);
873 yasm_vps_append(&vps, vp);
874 get_next_token(); /* STRING */
875
876 yasm_object_directive(p_object, ".file", "gas", &vps, NULL,
877 cur_line);
878
879 yasm_vps_delete(&vps);
880 return NULL;
881}

903static yasm_bytecode *
904parse_instr(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
905{
906 yasm_bytecode *bc;
907 char *id;
908 uintptr_t prefix;
909
910 if (parser_gas->intel_syntax) {
911 bc = parse_instr_intel(parser_gas);
912 if (bc) {
913 yasm_warn_disable(YASM_WARN_UNREC_CHAR);
914 do {
915 destroy_curtok();
916 get_next_token();
917 } while (!is_eol());
918 yasm_warn_enable(YASM_WARN_UNREC_CHAR);
919 }
920 return bc;
921 }
922
923 if (curtok != ID)
924 return NULL;
925
926 id = ID_val;
927
928 /* instructions/prefixes must start with a letter */
929 if (!isalpha(id[0]))
930 return NULL;
931
932 /* check to be sure it's not a label or equ */
933 get_peek_token(parser_gas);
934 if (parser_gas->peek_token == ':' || parser_gas->peek_token == '=')
935 return NULL;
936
937 switch (yasm_arch_parse_check_insnprefix
938 (p_object->arch, ID_val, ID_len, cur_line, &bc, &prefix)) {
939 case YASM_ARCH_INSN:
940 {
941 yasm_insn *insn;
942
943 /* Propagate errors in case we got a warning from the arch */
944 yasm_errwarn_propagate(parser_gas->errwarns, cur_line);
945
946 insn = yasm_bc_get_insn(bc);
947
948 yasm_xfree(id);
949 get_next_token(); /* ID */
950 if (is_eol())
951 return bc; /* no operands */
952
953 /* parse operands */
954 for (;;) {
955 yasm_insn_operand *op = parse_operand(parser_gas);
956 if (!op) {
957 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
958 N_("expression syntax error"));
959 yasm_bc_destroy(bc);
960 return NULL;
961 }
962 yasm_insn_ops_append(insn, op);
963
964 if (is_eol())
965 break;
966 if (!expect(',')) {
967 yasm_bc_destroy(bc);
968 return NULL;
969 }
970 get_next_token();
971 }
972 return bc;
973 }
974 case YASM_ARCH_PREFIX:
975 /* Propagate errors in case we got a warning from the arch */
976 yasm_errwarn_propagate(parser_gas->errwarns, cur_line);
977
978 yasm_xfree(id);
979 get_next_token(); /* ID */
980 bc = parse_instr(parser_gas);
981 if (!bc)
982 bc = yasm_arch_create_empty_insn(p_object->arch, cur_line);
983 yasm_insn_add_prefix(yasm_bc_get_insn(bc), prefix);
984 return bc;
985 default:
986 break;
987 }
988
989 /* Check for segment register used as prefix */
990 switch (yasm_arch_parse_check_regtmod(p_object->arch, ID_val, ID_len,
991 &prefix)) {
992 case YASM_ARCH_SEGREG:
993 yasm_xfree(id);
994 get_next_token(); /* ID */
995 bc = parse_instr(parser_gas);
996 if (!bc)
997 bc = yasm_arch_create_empty_insn(p_object->arch, cur_line);
998 yasm_insn_add_seg_prefix(yasm_bc_get_insn(bc), prefix);
999 return bc;
1000 default:
1001 return NULL;
1002 }
1003}
1004
1005static int
1006parse_dirvals(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, yasm_valparamhead *vps)
1007{
1008 yasm_valparam *vp;
1009 yasm_expr *e;
1010 int num = 0;
1011
1012 yasm_vps_initialize(vps);
1013
1014 for (;;) {
1015 switch (curtok) {
1016 case ID:
1017 get_peek_token(parser_gas);
1018 switch (parser_gas->peek_token) {
1019 case '+': case '-':
1020 case '|': case '^': case '&': case '!':
1021 case '*': case '/': case '%': case LEFT_OP: case RIGHT_OP:
1022 e = parse_expr(parser_gas);
1023 vp = yasm_vp_create_expr(NULL, e);
1024 break;
1025 default:
1026 /* Just an ID */
1027 vp = yasm_vp_create_id(NULL, ID_val, '\0');
1028 get_next_token(); /* ID */
1029 break;
1030 }
1031 break;
1032 case STRING:
1033 vp = yasm_vp_create_string(NULL, STRING_val.contents);
1034 get_next_token(); /* STRING */
1035 break;
1036 case REG:
1037 e = p_expr_new_ident(yasm_expr_reg(REG_val));
1038 vp = yasm_vp_create_expr(NULL, e);
1039 get_next_token(); /* REG */
1040 break;
1041 case '@':
1042 /* XXX: is throwing it away *really* the right thing? */
1043 get_next_token(); /* @ */
1044 continue;
1045 default:
1046 e = parse_expr(parser_gas);
1047 if (!e)
1048 return num;
1049 vp = yasm_vp_create_expr(NULL, e);
1050 break;
1051 }
1052 yasm_vps_append(vps, vp);
1053 num++;
1054 if (curtok == ',')
1055 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
1056 }
1057 return num;
1058}

1111/* instruction operands */
1112/* memory addresses */
1113static yasm_effaddr *
1114parse_memaddr(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
1115{
1116 yasm_effaddr *ea = NULL;
1117 yasm_expr *e1, *e2;
1118 int strong = 0;
1119
1120 if (curtok == SEGREG) {
1121 uintptr_t segreg = SEGREG_val;
1122 get_next_token(); /* SEGREG */
1123 if (!expect(':')) return NULL;
1124 get_next_token(); /* ':' */
1125 ea = parse_memaddr(parser_gas);
1126 if (!ea)
1127 return NULL;
1128 yasm_ea_set_segreg(ea, segreg);
1129 return ea;
1130 }
1131
1132 /* We want to parse a leading expression, except when it's actually
1133 * just a memory address (with no preceding expression) such as
1134 * (REG...) or (,...).
1135 */
1136 get_peek_token(parser_gas);
1137 if (curtok != '(' || (parser_gas->peek_token != REG
1138 && parser_gas->peek_token != ','))
1139 e1 = parse_expr(parser_gas);
1140 else
1141 e1 = NULL;
1142
1143 if (curtok == '(') {
1144 int havereg = 0;
1145 uintptr_t reg = 0;
1146 yasm_intnum *scale = NULL;
1147
1148 get_next_token(); /* '(' */
1149
1150 /* base register */
1151 if (curtok == REG) {
1152 e2 = p_expr_new_ident(yasm_expr_reg(REG_val));
1153 get_next_token(); /* REG */
1154 } else
1155 e2 = p_expr_new_ident(yasm_expr_int(yasm_intnum_create_uint(0)));
1156
1157 if (curtok == ')')
1158 goto done;
1159
1160 if (!expect(',')) {
1161 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("invalid memory expression"));
1162 if (e1) yasm_expr_destroy(e1);
1163 yasm_expr_destroy(e2);
1164 return NULL;
1165 }
1166 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
1167
1168 if (curtok == ')')
1169 goto done;
1170
1171 /* index register */
1172 if (curtok == REG) {
1173 reg = REG_val;
1174 havereg = 1;
1175 get_next_token(); /* REG */
1176 if (curtok != ',') {
1177 scale = yasm_intnum_create_uint(1);
1178 goto done;
1179 }
1180 get_next_token(); /* ',' */
1181 }
1182
1183 /* scale */
1184 if (!expect(INTNUM)) {
1185 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("non-integer scale"));
1186 if (e1) yasm_expr_destroy(e1);
1187 yasm_expr_destroy(e2);
1188 return NULL;
1189 }
1190 scale = INTNUM_val;
1191 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
1192
1193done:
1194 if (!expect(')')) {
1195 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("invalid memory expression"));
1196 if (scale) yasm_intnum_destroy(scale);
1197 if (e1) yasm_expr_destroy(e1);
1198 yasm_expr_destroy(e2);
1199 return NULL;
1200 }
1201 get_next_token(); /* ')' */
1202
1203 if (scale) {
1204 if (!havereg) {
1205 if (yasm_intnum_get_uint(scale) != 1)
1206 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1207 N_("scale factor of %u without an index register"),
1208 yasm_intnum_get_uint(scale));
1209 yasm_intnum_destroy(scale);
1210 } else
1211 e2 = p_expr_new(yasm_expr_expr(e2), YASM_EXPR_ADD,
1212 yasm_expr_expr(p_expr_new(yasm_expr_reg(reg), YASM_EXPR_MUL,
1213 yasm_expr_int(scale))));
1214 }
1215
1216 if (e1) {
1217 /* Ordering is critical here to correctly detecting presence of
1218 * RIP in RIP-relative expressions.
1219 */
1220 e1 = p_expr_new_tree(e2, YASM_EXPR_ADD, e1);
1221 } else
1222 e1 = e2;
1223 strong = 1;
1224 }
1225
1226 if (!e1)
1227 return NULL;
1228 ea = yasm_arch_ea_create(p_object->arch, e1);
1229 if (strong)
1230 ea->strong = 1;
1231 return ea;
1232}
1233
1234static yasm_insn_operand *
1235parse_operand(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
1236{
1237 yasm_effaddr *ea;
1238 yasm_insn_operand *op;
1239 uintptr_t reg;
1240
1241 switch (curtok) {
1242 case REG:
1243 reg = REG_val;
1244 get_next_token(); /* REG */
1245 return yasm_operand_create_reg(reg);
1246 case SEGREG:
1247 /* need to see if it's really a memory address */
1248 get_peek_token(parser_gas);
1249 if (parser_gas->peek_token == ':') {
1250 ea = parse_memaddr(parser_gas);
1251 if (!ea)
1252 return NULL;
1253 return yasm_operand_create_mem(ea);
1254 }
1255 reg = SEGREG_val;
1256 get_next_token(); /* SEGREG */
1257 return yasm_operand_create_segreg(reg);
1258 case REGGROUP:
1259 {
1260 unsigned long regindex;
1261 reg = REGGROUP_val;
1262 get_next_token(); /* REGGROUP */
1263 if (curtok != '(')
1264 return yasm_operand_create_reg(reg);
1265 get_next_token(); /* '(' */
1266 if (!expect(INTNUM)) {
1267 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
1268 N_("integer register index expected"));
1269 return NULL;
1270 }
1271 regindex = yasm_intnum_get_uint(INTNUM_val);
1272 get_next_token(); /* INTNUM */
1273 if (!expect(')')) {
1274 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
1275 N_("missing closing parenthesis for register index"));
1276 return NULL;
1277 }
1278 get_next_token(); /* ')' */
1279 reg = yasm_arch_reggroup_get_reg(p_object->arch, reg, regindex);
1280 if (reg == 0) {
1281 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("bad register index `%u'"),
1282 regindex);
1283 return NULL;
1284 }
1285 return yasm_operand_create_reg(reg);
1286 }
1287 case '$':
1288 {
1289 yasm_expr *e;
1290 get_next_token(); /* '$' */
1291 e = parse_expr(parser_gas);
1292 if (!e) {
1293 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
1294 N_("expression missing after `%s'"), "$");
1295 return NULL;
1296 }
1297 return yasm_operand_create_imm(e);
1298 }
1299 case '*':
1300 get_next_token(); /* '*' */
1301 if (curtok == REG) {
1302 op = yasm_operand_create_reg(REG_val);
1303 get_next_token(); /* REG */
1304 } else {
1305 ea = parse_memaddr(parser_gas);
1306 if (!ea) {
1307 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
1308 N_("expression missing after `%s'"), "*");
1309 return NULL;
1310 }
1311 op = yasm_operand_create_mem(ea);
1312 }
1313 op->deref = 1;
1314 return op;
1315 default:
1316 ea = parse_memaddr(parser_gas);
1317 if (!ea)
1318 return NULL;
1319 return yasm_operand_create_mem(ea);
1320 }
1321}
1322
1323/* Expression grammar parsed is:
1324 *
1325 * expr : expr0 [ {+,-} expr0...]
1326 * expr0 : expr1 [ {|,^,&,!} expr1...]
1327 * expr1 : expr2 [ {*,/,%,<<,>>} expr2...]
1328 * expr2 : { ~,+,- } expr2
1329 * | (expr)
1330 * | symbol
1331 * | number
1332 */
1333
1334static yasm_expr *
1335parse_expr(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
1336{
1337 yasm_expr *e, *f;
1338 e = parse_expr0(parser_gas);
1339 if (!e)
1340 return NULL;
1341
1342 while (curtok == '+' || curtok == '-') {
1343 int op = curtok;
1344 get_next_token();
1345 f = parse_expr0(parser_gas);
1346 if (!f) {
1347 yasm_expr_destroy(e);
1348 return NULL;
1349 }
1350
1351 switch (op) {
1352 case '+': e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_ADD, f); break;
1353 case '-': e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_SUB, f); break;
1354 }
1355 }
1356 return e;
1357}
1358
1359static yasm_expr *
1360parse_expr0(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
1361{
1362 yasm_expr *e, *f;
1363 e = parse_expr1(parser_gas);
1364 if (!e)
1365 return NULL;
1366
1367 while (curtok == '|' || curtok == '^' || curtok == '&' || curtok == '!') {
1368 int op = curtok;
1369 get_next_token();
1370 f = parse_expr1(parser_gas);
1371 if (!f) {
1372 yasm_expr_destroy(e);
1373 return NULL;
1374 }
1375
1376 switch (op) {
1377 case '|': e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_OR, f); break;
1378 case '^': e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_XOR, f); break;
1379 case '&': e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_AND, f); break;
1380 case '!': e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_NOR, f); break;
1381 }
1382 }
1383 return e;
1384}
1385
1386static yasm_expr *
1387parse_expr1(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
1388{
1389 yasm_expr *e, *f;
1390 e = parse_expr2(parser_gas);
1391 if (!e)
1392 return NULL;
1393
1394 while (curtok == '*' || curtok == '/' || curtok == '%' || curtok == LEFT_OP
1395 || curtok == RIGHT_OP) {
1396 int op = curtok;
1397 get_next_token();
1398 f = parse_expr2(parser_gas);
1399 if (!f) {
1400 yasm_expr_destroy(e);
1401 return NULL;
1402 }
1403
1404 switch (op) {
1405 case '*': e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_MUL, f); break;
1406 case '/': e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_DIV, f); break;
1407 case '%': e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_MOD, f); break;
1408 case LEFT_OP: e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_SHL, f); break;
1409 case RIGHT_OP: e = p_expr_new_tree(e, YASM_EXPR_SHR, f); break;
1410 }
1411 }
1412 return e;
1413}
1414
1415static yasm_expr *
1416parse_expr2(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
1417{
1418 yasm_expr *e;
1419 yasm_symrec *sym;
1420
1421 switch (curtok) {
1422 case '+':
1423 get_next_token();
1424 return parse_expr2(parser_gas);
1425 case '-':
1426 get_next_token();
1427 e = parse_expr2(parser_gas);
1428 if (!e)
1429 return NULL;
1430 return p_expr_new_branch(YASM_EXPR_NEG, e);
1431 case '~':
1432 get_next_token();
1433 e = parse_expr2(parser_gas);
1434 if (!e)
1435 return NULL;
1436 return p_expr_new_branch(YASM_EXPR_NOT, e);
1437 case '(':
1438 get_next_token();
1439 e = parse_expr(parser_gas);
1440 if (!e)
1441 return NULL;
1442 if (!expect(')')) {
1443 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("missing parenthesis"));
1444 return NULL;
1445 }
1446 get_next_token();
1447 return e;
1448 case INTNUM:
1449 e = p_expr_new_ident(yasm_expr_int(INTNUM_val));
1450 get_next_token();
1451 return e;
1452 case FLTNUM:
1453 e = p_expr_new_ident(yasm_expr_float(FLTNUM_val));
1454 get_next_token();
1455 return e;
1456 case ID:
1457 {
1458 char *name = ID_val;
1459 get_next_token(); /* ID */
1460
1461 /* "." references the current assembly position */
1462 if (name[1] == '\0' && name[0] == '.')
1463 sym = yasm_symtab_define_curpos(p_symtab, ".",
1464 parser_gas->prev_bc, cur_line);
1465 else
1466 sym = yasm_symtab_use(p_symtab, name, cur_line);
1467 yasm_xfree(name);
1468
1469 if (curtok == '@') {
1470 yasm_symrec *wrt;
1471 /* TODO: this is needed for shared objects, e.g. sym@PLT */
1472 get_next_token(); /* '@' */
1473 if (!expect(ID)) {
1474 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
1475 N_("expected identifier after `@'"));
1476 return NULL;
1477 }
1478 wrt = yasm_objfmt_get_special_sym(p_object, ID_val, "gas");
1479 yasm_xfree(ID_val);
1480 get_next_token(); /* ID */
1481 if (!wrt) {
1482 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1483 N_("unrecognized identifier after `@'"));
1484 return p_expr_new_ident(yasm_expr_sym(sym));
1485 }
1486 return p_expr_new(yasm_expr_sym(sym), YASM_EXPR_WRT,
1487 yasm_expr_sym(wrt));
1488 }
1489
1490 return p_expr_new_ident(yasm_expr_sym(sym));
1491 }
1492 default:
1493 return NULL;
1494 }
1495}

1497static void
1498define_label(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, char *name, int local)
1499{
1500 if (!local) {
1501 if (parser_gas->locallabel_base)
1502 yasm_xfree(parser_gas->locallabel_base);
1503 parser_gas->locallabel_base_len = strlen(name);
1504 parser_gas->locallabel_base =
1505 yasm_xmalloc(parser_gas->locallabel_base_len+1);
1506 strcpy(parser_gas->locallabel_base, name);
1507 }
1508
1509 yasm_symtab_define_label(p_symtab, name, parser_gas->prev_bc, 1,
1510 cur_line);
1511 yasm_xfree(name);
1512}

1514static void
1515define_lcomm(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, /*@only@*/ char *name,
1516 yasm_expr *size, /*@null@*/ yasm_expr *align)
1517{
1518 /* Put into .bss section. */
1519 /*@dependent@*/ yasm_section *bss =
1520 gas_get_section(parser_gas, yasm__xstrdup(".bss"), NULL, NULL, NULL, 1);
1521
1522 if (align) {
1523 /* XXX: assume alignment is in bytes, not power-of-two */
1524 yasm_section_bcs_append(bss, gas_parser_align(parser_gas, bss, align,
1525 NULL, NULL, 0));
1526 }
1527
1528 yasm_symtab_define_label(p_symtab, name, yasm_section_bcs_last(bss), 1,
1529 cur_line);
1530 yasm_section_bcs_append(bss, yasm_bc_create_reserve(size, 1, cur_line));
1531 yasm_xfree(name);
1532}

1534static yasm_section *
1535gas_get_section(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, char *name,
1536 /*@null@*/ char *flags, /*@null@*/ char *type,
1537 /*@null@*/ yasm_valparamhead *objext_valparams,
1538 int builtin)
1539{
1540 yasm_valparamhead vps;
1541 yasm_valparam *vp;
1542 char *gasflags;
1543 yasm_section *new_section;
1544
1545 yasm_vps_initialize(&vps);
1546 vp = yasm_vp_create_id(NULL, name, '\0');
1547 yasm_vps_append(&vps, vp);
1548
1549 if (!builtin) {
1550 if (flags)
1551 gasflags = yasm__xstrdup(flags);
1552 else
1553 gasflags = yasm__xstrdup("");
1554 vp = yasm_vp_create_string(yasm__xstrdup("gasflags"), gasflags);
1555 yasm_vps_append(&vps, vp);
1556 if (type) {
1557 vp = yasm_vp_create_id(NULL, type, '\0');
1558 yasm_vps_append(&vps, vp);
1559 }
1560 }
1561
1562 new_section = yasm_objfmt_section_switch(p_object, &vps, objext_valparams,
1563 cur_line);
1564
1565 yasm_vps_delete(&vps);
1566 return new_section;
1567}

1569static void
1570gas_switch_section(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, const char *name,
1571 /*@null@*/ char *flags, /*@null@*/ char *type,
1572 /*@null@*/ yasm_valparamhead *objext_valparams,
1573 int builtin)
1574{
1575 yasm_section *new_section;
1576
1577 new_section = gas_get_section(parser_gas, yasm__xstrdup(name), flags, type,
1578 objext_valparams, builtin);
1579 if (new_section) {
1580 cursect = new_section;
1581 parser_gas->prev_bc = yasm_section_bcs_last(new_section);
1582 } else
1583 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_GENERAL, N_("invalid section name `%s'"),
1584 name);
1585
1586 if (objext_valparams)
1587 yasm_vps_delete(objext_valparams);
1588}

1590static yasm_bytecode *
1591gas_parser_align(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, yasm_section *sect,
1592 yasm_expr *boundval, /*@null@*/ yasm_expr *fillval,
1593 /*@null@*/ yasm_expr *maxskipval, int power2)
1594{
1595 yasm_intnum *boundintn;
1596
1597 /* Convert power of two to number of bytes if necessary */
1598 if (power2)
1599 boundval = yasm_expr_create(YASM_EXPR_SHL,
1600 yasm_expr_int(yasm_intnum_create_uint(1)),
1601 yasm_expr_expr(boundval), cur_line);
1602
1603 /* Largest .align in the section specifies section alignment. */
1604 boundintn = yasm_expr_get_intnum(&boundval, 0);
1605 if (boundintn) {
1606 unsigned long boundint = yasm_intnum_get_uint(boundintn);
1607
1608 /* Alignments must be a power of two. */
1609 if (is_exp2(boundint)) {
1610 if (boundint > yasm_section_get_align(sect))
1611 yasm_section_set_align(sect, boundint, cur_line);
1612 }
1613 }
1614
1615 return yasm_bc_create_align(boundval, fillval, maxskipval,
1616 yasm_section_is_code(sect) ?
1617 yasm_arch_get_fill(p_object->arch) : NULL,
1618 cur_line);
1619}

1621static yasm_bytecode *
1622gas_parser_dir_fill(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, /*@only@*/ yasm_expr *repeat,
1623 /*@only@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_expr *size,
1624 /*@only@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_expr *value)
1625{
1626 yasm_datavalhead dvs;
1627 yasm_bytecode *bc;
1628 unsigned int ssize;
1629
1630 if (size) {
1631 /*@dependent@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_intnum *intn;
1632 intn = yasm_expr_get_intnum(&size, 0);
1633 if (!intn) {
1634 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_NOT_ABSOLUTE,
1635 N_("size must be an absolute expression"));
1636 yasm_expr_destroy(repeat);
1637 yasm_expr_destroy(size);
1638 if (value)
1639 yasm_expr_destroy(value);
1640 return NULL;
1641 }
1642 ssize = yasm_intnum_get_uint(intn);
1643 } else
1644 ssize = 1;
1645
1646 if (!value)
1647 value = yasm_expr_create_ident(
1648 yasm_expr_int(yasm_intnum_create_uint(0)), cur_line);
1649
1650 yasm_dvs_initialize(&dvs);
1651 yasm_dvs_append(&dvs, yasm_dv_create_expr(value));
1652 bc = yasm_bc_create_data(&dvs, ssize, 0, p_object->arch, cur_line);
1653
1654 yasm_bc_set_multiple(bc, repeat);
1655
1656 return bc;
1657}

1721void
1722gas_parser_parse(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas)
1723{
1724 dir_lookup word;
1725 unsigned int i;
1726 int replace = 1;
1727
1728 word.name = ".word";
1729 word.handler = dir_data;
1730 word.param = yasm_arch_wordsize(p_object->arch)/8;
1731 word.newstate = INITIAL;
1732
1733 /* Create directive lookup */
1734 parser_gas->dirs = HAMT_create(1, yasm_internal_error_);
1735 HAMT_insert(parser_gas->dirs, word.name, &word, &replace, no_delete);
1736 for (i=0; i<NELEMS(dirs_static); i++) {
1737 replace = 1;
1738 HAMT_insert(parser_gas->dirs, dirs_static[i].name,
1739 &dirs_static[i], &replace, no_delete);
1740 }
1741
1742 while (get_next_token() != 0) {
1743 yasm_bytecode *bc = NULL, *temp_bc;
1744
1745 if (!is_eol()) {
1746 bc = parse_line(parser_gas);
1747 demand_eol();
1748 }
1749
1750 yasm_errwarn_propagate(parser_gas->errwarns, cur_line);
1751
1752 temp_bc = yasm_section_bcs_append(cursect, bc);
1753 if (temp_bc)
1754 parser_gas->prev_bc = temp_bc;
1755 if (curtok == ';')
1756 continue; /* don't advance line number until \n */
1757 if (parser_gas->save_input)
1758 yasm_linemap_add_source(parser_gas->linemap,
1759 temp_bc,
1760 (char *)parser_gas->save_line[parser_gas->save_last ^ 1]);
1761 yasm_linemap_goto_next(parser_gas->linemap);
1762 parser_gas->dir_line++; /* keep track for .line followed by .file */
1763 }
1764
1765 HAMT_destroy(parser_gas->dirs, no_delete);
1766}
